def: The quality or state of being portable; fitness to be carried.
Capable of being imparted or communicated.
A panorama of the interior of a building, seen from within.
The quality or state of being servile; servileness.To be a queen in bondage is more vile Than is a slave in baseservility. Shak.
One who, or that which, distracts away.
A suborder of carnivorous and insectivorous marsupialsincluding the dasyures and the opossums.
pertaining to, or obtained from, rue (Ruta); as, rutic acid,now commonly called capric acid.

Not energetic or exact in duty or business; not careful orprompt in fulfilling engagements; negligent; careless; tardy;behindhand; lagging; slack; hence, lacking earnestness or activity;languid; slow.Thou never wast remiss, I bear thee witness. Milton.These nervous, bold; those languid and remiss. Roscommon.Its motion becomes more languid and remiss. Woodward.
